<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1324,283,1110]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,662,283,309]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Description (minor worker)</emphasis>
. Posterolateral margin of head angular, the dorsal surface weakly convex, the lateral surface weakly concave, a ridge running from just below the eye to the posterolateral corner. Petiolar node tapering dorsally into a blunt angle. Individual erect hairs scattered on dorsum of mesosoma, petiole and gaster; enlarged yellow hairs present on central region of the gastral dorsum; pubescence abundant on entire body. Colour black, gaster dark red­black, legs dark red.
</paragraph>
